> /*
>  * Per-paint-cycle byte alignment offset for the dirty-rect path.
>  *
>  * When screen_start is not a multiple of 4 (which Keen 4-style byte-level
>  * scrolling routinely produces), the dirty mark machinery loses the bottom
>  * 2 bits of every byte address via the `>>2` shift used to index video_copy.
>  * search_video_copy then records video_copy_offset in 4-byte-chunk units,
>  * and paint_records reconstructs a memory address that's off by up to 3 bytes
>  * (= up to 24 pixels of horizontal shift).
>  *
>  * The caller (ega_split_graph_update / ega_graph_update) sets this to
>  * (screen_start & 3) before each paint_records call for upper-half records,
>  * and to 0 for lower-half records (whose lines start at the 4-byte-aligned
>  * base offset 0). paint_records adds it to the offset passed to paint_screen
>  * so the source bytes match what the full-refresh path would read.
>  */
> GLOBAL int      current_paint_alignment = 0;
